<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU3"></a><font style="font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">SIGNATURES </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Pursuant to the requirements of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934, the registrant has duly caused this report to be signed on its behalf by the undersigned hereunto duly authorized. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:12pt;font-family:Times New Roman;">&nbsp;</p>
<div align="right">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" style="border-collapse:collapse; width:45%;">

<td valign="bottom"  style="width:2.22%;">

<td valign="top"  style="width:84.44%;">

<body>

<p style="text-align:right;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:12pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Exhibit 99.1</p>
<p style="text-align:right;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<div>
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="center" style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="middle"  style="width:18.88%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:11pt;font-family:Calibri;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><img src="g2018020720565996738241.jpg" title="" alt="" style="width:128px;height:172px;"></p></td>
<td valign="top"  style="width:81.12%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:18pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Tesla Fourth Quarter &amp; Full Year 2017 Update</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;margin-left:18pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#x2022;<font style="font-weight:bold;font-family:Arial;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Record Model S and Model X deliveries in Q4 2017</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:18pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#x2022;<font style="font-weight:bold;font-family:Arial;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Cash balance of $3.4B entering Q1 2018</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:18pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#x2022;<font style="font-weight:bold;font-family:Arial;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;2017 revenue of $11.8B, up 55% y-o-y from organic growth</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:18pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#x2022;<font style="font-weight:bold;font-family:Arial;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;2018 revenue growth expected to significantly exceed 2017 growth</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:18pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#x2022;<font style="font-weight:bold;font-family:Arial;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Continuing to target Model 3 production rate of 5,000/wk by Q2 end</font></p></td>
</tr>
</table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:9pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">2017 was an important year in Tesla&#8217;s history.&nbsp;&nbsp;Among other things, we started delivering Model 3 to customers, unveiled the Semi and the next-generation Roadster, installed the world&#8217;s largest battery in Australia, and had record vehicle production and deliveries of Model S and Model X.&nbsp;&nbsp;We also learned many lessons from the slower than planned production ramp of Model 3. All of this sets the stage for 2018 to be a transformative year for us.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:9pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">At some point in 2018, we expect to begin generating positive quarterly operating income on a sustained basis. With the planned ramp of both Model 3 and our energy storage products, our rate of revenue growth this year is poised to significantly exceed last year&#8217;s growth rate.&nbsp;&nbsp;The launch of Model 3 is what Tesla had been building towards from day one.&nbsp;&nbsp;We incorporated all the learnings from the development and production of Roadster, Model S, and Model X to create the world&#8217;s first mass market electric vehicle that is priced on par with its gasoline-powered equivalents &#8211; even without incentives.&nbsp;&nbsp;Now we are ramping up production significantly, and as we look ahead in 2018, we are on the cusp of a step change in the world&#8217;s transition to sustainability.  </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<div>
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="center" style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="middle"  style="width:50%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;font-size:9pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="text-decoration:underline;">ADVANCING SUSTAINABLE TRANSPORT</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:9pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">We continue to target weekly Model 3 production rates of 2,500 by the end of Q1 and 5,000 by the end of Q2.  It is important to note that while these are the levels we are focused on hitting and we have plans in place to achieve them, our prior experience on the Model 3 ramp has demonstrated the difficulty of accurately forecasting specific production rates at specific points in time.  What we can say with confidence is that we are taking many actions to systematically address bottlenecks and add capacity in places like the battery module line where we have experienced constraints, and these actions should result in our production rate significantly increasing during the rest of Q1 and through Q2.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:9pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Our goal is to become the best manufacturer in the automotive industry, and having cutting edge robotic expertise in-house is at the core of that goal.&nbsp;&nbsp;Our recent acquisitions of advanced automation companies have added to our talent base and are helping us increase Model 3 production rates more effectively.&nbsp;&nbsp;We don&#8217;t want to simply replicate what we have built previously while designing additional capacity.  We want to continuously push the boundaries of mass manufacturing. </p></td>
<td valign="top"  style="width:50%;">
<p style="text-align:right;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:11pt;font-family:Calibri;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><img src="g2018020720565998938242.jpg" title="" alt="" style="width:361px;height:262px;"></p></td>
</tr>
</table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:9pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">As we shared previously, in order to incorporate our learnings and be capital efficient, we intend to start adding enough capacity to get to a 10,000 unit weekly rate for Model 3 once we have first hit the 5,000 per week milestone.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:9pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Despite the delays that we experienced in our production ramp, Model 3 net reservations remained stable in Q4.&nbsp;&nbsp;In recent weeks, they have continued to grow as Model 3 has arrived in select Tesla stores and received numerous positive reviews, including Automobile Magazine&#8217;s 2018 Design of the Year award.&nbsp;&nbsp;We want to thank both our Model 3 suppliers and our customers, who have continued to be such great partners and advocates, while patiently waiting as the ramp continues to accelerate.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:9pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">In Q4, we delivered 28,425 Model S and Model X vehicles and 1,542 Model 3 vehicles, totaling 29,967 deliveries.  Combined Model S and Model X deliveries in Q4 grew 10% globally compared to our prior record in Q3, and they grew 28% compared to Q4 2016.  As we indicated heading into Q4, production of Model S and Model X during the quarter was limited to 22,137 vehicles due to reallocation of some of the manufacturing resources to Model 3 production.&nbsp;&nbsp;This enabled us to reduce our finished-goods inventory to the lowest level in about 18 months.  </p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<div>
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="center" style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="middle"  style="width:50%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:9pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Combined Model S and Model X net orders in Q4 were just shy of Q3&#8217;s all-time high.&nbsp;&nbsp;Importantly, combined orders for Model S and Model X grew significantly in 2017 compared to 2016.&nbsp;&nbsp;There had initially been concerns about whether Model 3 would cannibalize Model S and Model X.&nbsp;&nbsp;It seems the opposite is true.&nbsp;&nbsp;In stores where Model 3 is on display, customer foot traffic has increased considerably and orders for Model S and Model X have in fact increased.&nbsp;&nbsp;There has been an even bigger increase in solar and Powerwall sales. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:9pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The upcoming autonomous coast-to-coast drive will showcase a major leap forward for our self-driving technology.  Additionally, an extensive overhaul of the underlying architecture of our software has now been completed, which has enabled a step-change improvement in the collection and analysis of data and fundamentally enhanced its machine learning capabilities.&nbsp;&nbsp;Our neural net, which expands as our customer fleet grows, is able to collect and analyze more high-quality data than ever before, enabling us to rollout a series of new Autopilot features in 2018 and beyond.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top"  style="width:50%;">
<p style="text-align:right;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:11pt;font-family:Calibri;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><img src="g2018020720570007638243.jpg" title="" alt="" style="width:361px;height:276px;"></p></td>
</tr>
</table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:9pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">During Q4, we opened 12 new store and service locations resulting in 330 total locations worldwide at the end of the year.&nbsp;&nbsp;Service capacity more than doubled in 2017, partially due to new locations, but also through a 50% increase in productivity of existing service locations, as well as the significant expansion of our Mobile Service fleet, which now has 230 vehicles.&nbsp;&nbsp;We strive to create the best car ownership experience on the planet, and a big part of that is through not requiring customers to come in to service their vehicle.&nbsp;&nbsp;In North America alone, Mobile Service is now completing 30% of all service jobs, allowing those customers to never have to leave their home or office to get their cars serviced.&nbsp;&nbsp;Not surprisingly, Mobile Service has achieved customer satisfaction that averages 98%.&nbsp;&nbsp;In addition, the cost of servicing with our Mobile Service fleet is significantly lower than from our service centers.&nbsp;&nbsp;It now covers all of North America and provides a level of convenience and a speed for scaling that is unique and unprecedented in the industry.&nbsp;&nbsp;In 2018, we will continue to increase our service capacity with the goal of always remaining ahead of the Model 3 ramp. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:9pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Our Supercharger network has seen the most significant growth yet.&nbsp;&nbsp;In 2017, 338 new locations opened for a total of 1,128 Supercharger stations globally.&nbsp;&nbsp;Between Supercharger and Destination Charging, we increased capacity by over 90%.  In preparation for Model 3, we opened several large Supercharger stations along our most popular corridors, including between Los Angeles and San Francisco and between Los Angeles and Las Vegas, both of which have a customer lounge, a caf&#233;, a display of our energy products and 40 charging stalls.&nbsp;&nbsp;With continued emphasis on convenient, reliable, and ubiquitous charging, 2018 will be another big year for Tesla charging infrastructure.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<div>
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="center" style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top"  style="width:50%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:11pt;font-family:Calibri;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><img src="g2018020720570009138244.jpg" title="" alt="" style="width:361px;height:270px;"></p></td>
<td valign="top"  style="width:50%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:9pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The unveiling of Tesla Semi on November 16 launched Tesla into a new product category that will have a transformative impact due to a total cost of ownership that is superior to diesel trucks.  Tesla Semi combines a real-world range of up to 500 miles with unprecedented performance while pulling a standard payload.&nbsp;&nbsp;Its distinctive torque enables smooth acceleration to highway speed even when fully loaded with cargo.&nbsp;&nbsp;Moreover, it has been designed to dramatically improve safety not only for the driver and cargo, but also for pedestrians and other cars on the road.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:9pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Tesla will be the first Semi customer.&nbsp;&nbsp;We plan to use the Tesla Semi for our own logistics by transporting Model 3 components from Gigafactory 1 to Fremont.&nbsp;&nbsp;Additionally, our initial fleet customers who placed reservations for the Tesla Semi have been helping us develop the best possible truck.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:9pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Also, after developing it in stealth with a very small team, we were thrilled to surprise everyone with the next-generation Roadster.&nbsp;&nbsp;Roadster was at the genesis of Tesla, a car that proved electric vehicles can be fast, exciting and here to stay.&nbsp;&nbsp;The new Roadster takes this concept to the next level.&nbsp;&nbsp;With 0-60 mph acceleration of 1.9 seconds and maximum speed of more than 250 mph, it will be the fastest car in the world.&nbsp;&nbsp;When that performance is combined with its 620 miles (1,000 km) of range, this supercar puts to rest any debate about the limitations of electric vehicles.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p></td>
</tr>
</table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;;font-size:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:9pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="text-decoration:underline;"><br /></font></p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="text-align:justify;margin-bottom:6pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:9pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU2"></a><font style="text-decoration:underline;">ADVANCING SUSTAINABLE ENERGY</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;color:#000000;font-size:9pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">2018 will see major growth in Tesla energy storage deployments, as the production ramp of our storage products is just as steep as with Model 3.&nbsp;&nbsp;This year, we aim to deploy at least three times the storage capacity we deployed in 2017.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;color:#000000;font-size:9pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">On December 1, 2017, installation of the largest battery in the world was completed ahead of schedule in South Australia.&nbsp;&nbsp;This project is already generating substantial benefit by meeting high summer demand when supply is limited and by instantaneously responding to unplanned interruptions or frequency drops in the grid.&nbsp;&nbsp;Due to the success of this project, we're seeing an increase in demand for Powerpack, our commercial energy storage product.  With more electric utilities and governments around the world recognizing the reliability, environmental, and economic benefits of this product, it&#8217;s clear that there is a huge opportunity for us in large scale energy storage.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;color:#000000;font-size:9pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Powerwall demand for home energy storage remains exceptionally high, with orders consistently above production levels.&nbsp;&nbsp;We are increasingly promoting our energy products in Tesla stores and in non-Tesla retail locations.&nbsp;&nbsp;There is a significant cross-selling potential between Powerwall and our solar products, as evidenced by the fact that a vast majority of the customers who have ordered Solar Roof have also ordered at least one Powerwall.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<div>
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="center" style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top"  style="width:50%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:11pt;font-family:Calibri;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><img src="g2018020720570011138245.jpg" title="" alt="" style="width:359px;height:268px;"></p></td>
<td valign="top"  style="width:50%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;color:#000000;font-size:9pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">In Q4, we deployed 143 MWh of energy storage products, growing 45% from Q4 2016.&nbsp;&nbsp;Deployment of 129 MWh of energy storage in South Australia will be recognized in Q1 2018 based on commercial transfer of the site to the customer.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;color:#000000;font-size:9pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">We also deployed 87 MW of energy generation systems in Q4, which is 20% less than Q3 2017.&nbsp;&nbsp;Solar MW deployed declined as volumes continue to be impacted by our decision to close certain sales channels earlier this year and to focus on projects with better margins.&nbsp;&nbsp;In addition, solar deployments were affected by the short supply of Powerwalls for customers who wanted solar plus Powerwall in their house.&nbsp;&nbsp;While volumes may continue to be impacted by these factors over the near-term, we expect growth to resume later this year.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;color:#000000;font-size:9pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">We continue to ramp energy sales in Tesla retail stores and are expanding our presence in partner locations.&nbsp;&nbsp;The mix of our residential solar sales continues to shift towards cash and loan as compared to leasing, reaching 54% of total residential solar sales in Q4, up from 25% in Q4 2016.<font style="font-weight:bold;">  </font>This has contributed to improved cash performance of this business.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;;font-size:10.5pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
</tr>
</table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;color:#000000;font-size:9pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Initial production of Solar Roof at the Gigafactory 2 in Buffalo started in Q4, and we are ahead of schedule with the hiring targets we&#8217;ve agreed to with the state of New York.&nbsp;&nbsp;As Solar Roof is truly the first-of-its-kind and there is significant complexity in both its manufacturing and installation, we are deliberately ramping production at a gradual pace.&nbsp;&nbsp;When fully scaled, Gigafactory 2 will be able to produce enough solar cells to add more than 150,000 new residential solar installations every year.&nbsp;&nbsp;As we ramp production, a portion of the output will be dedicated for Solar Roof tiles with the balance used in our proprietary high-efficiency retrofit solar panels.&nbsp;&nbsp;With demand outpacing production, we expect our backlog to remain in excess of one year for the next several quarters. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;;font-size:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:9pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="text-decoration:underline;">Q4 2017 RESULTS </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;;font-size:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:9pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Revenue&#160;&amp; Gross Margin</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.33%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-size:9pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:9pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#x2022;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-size:9pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;">Automotive revenue in Q4 increased by 36% over Q4 2016, mainly due to 35% growth in vehicle deliveries.  For 2017, Automotive revenue was up 52% from 2016.&nbsp;&nbsp;ZEV credit sales in Q4 were $179 million as compared to $20 million in Q4 2016.&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.33%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-size:9pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:9pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#x2022;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-size:9pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;">Approximately 23% of Q4 deliveries were subject to lease accounting, which was slightly higher than in Q3.&nbsp;&nbsp;Last week, we closed a $546 million asset backed securitization (ABS) of our Model S and X lease portfolio, which was our first such offering.&nbsp;&nbsp;This transaction and future ones like it will free up significant leasing capacity for long-term growth.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:9pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><br /></p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.33%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-size:9pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:9pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#x2022;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-size:9pt;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU3"></a><font style="font-size:9pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"></font><font style="font-size:9pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"></font><font style="font-family:Arial;">GAAP Automotive gross margin improved slightly compared to Q3 to 18.9%.&nbsp;&nbsp;Non-GAAP Automotive gross margin declined to 13.8% in Q4, which was below our expectations.&nbsp;&nbsp;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;">This is more than fully explained by</font><font style="font-family:Arial;"> the s</font><font style="font-family:Arial;">lower than expected </font><font style="font-family:Arial;">ramp of </font><font style="font-family:Arial;">Model 3.&nbsp;&nbsp;Since Model 3 production was in the early stages of the ramp, allocation of full operating costs and depreciation made its gross margin negative.&nbsp;&nbsp;We are expecting a negative Model 3 gross margin in Q1, while generating positive operating cash flow</font><font style="font-family:Arial;">s</font><font style="font-family:Arial;">.&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.33%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-size:9pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:9pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#x2022;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-size:9pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;">Model S and Model X gross margin in Q4 declined very slightly compared to Q3.&nbsp;&nbsp;This was primarily due to significant reserves booked for fixed assets that are no longer in service.&nbsp;&nbsp;We expect Model S and Model X gross margins to increase in 2018 with improved trim mix and option content, lower cost of acquisition and lower manufacturing costs.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:3.33%;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.33%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-size:9pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:9pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#x2022;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-size:9pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;">Energy generation and storage revenue in Q4 decreased by 6% compared to Q3.  This was mainly driven by seasonal decline in solar deployment and by our continued focus on more profitable, cash sales. </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.33%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-size:9pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:9pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#x2022;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-size:9pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;">GAAP gross margin in Q4 declined significantly as compared to Q3, due largely to several one-time factors and a higher mix of storage products.&nbsp;&nbsp;Q4 gross margin was impacted by the typical seasonal decline in solar energy production and correspondingly lower lease revenue in the winter months. We also booked one-time air freight costs for the South Australian battery project and took write-downs related to legacy commercial &amp; industrial projects that we had committed to prior to the acquisition of SolarCity.&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">

<td valign="top" style="width:3.33%;white-space:nowrap">

<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-size:9pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;">We expect gross margin to improve significantly in 2018 from higher operational and manufacturing cost efficiencies as well as deployment of higher-quality commercial projects.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:9pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Other Highlights</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:-0.83%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.33%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-size:9pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:9pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#x2022;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-size:9pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;">Service and Other revenue decreased by 5% compared to Q3 but increased by 81% compared to Q4 2016.&nbsp;&nbsp;Used car sales was the main driver of this year-over-year growth.&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.33%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-size:9pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:9pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#x2022;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-size:9pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;">Service and Other gross loss increased to $89 million due to the significant growth of our service network in Q4 that has not been fully utilized yet as the Model 3 production ramp works to catch up, reserves for settlements with former customers of Grohmann and a one-time warranty true-up for used car sales.&nbsp;&nbsp;Gross margin on used cars sales was close to breakeven.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.33%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-size:9pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:9pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#x2022;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-size:9pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;">Operating expenses increased by 5% sequentially to a total of $1.04 billion in spite of significant revenue growth.&nbsp;&nbsp;We continue to focus on keeping tight control over operating expenses even as we ramp production.&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">

<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-size:9pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;">Basic shares outstanding at the end of Q4 were approximately 168 million.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>

<p style="text-align:justify;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:3.33%;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.33%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-size:9pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:9pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#x2022;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-size:9pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;">Cash flow from operating activities reached $510 million in Q4, achieving a new quarterly record.&nbsp;&nbsp;This was achieved mainly by improved collection of receivables, inventory reduction of finished vehicles, improved working capital from the ramp of Model 3, and growth in customer deposits.&nbsp;&nbsp;Cash flow from operating activities in 2017 was close to breakeven.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.33%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-size:9pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:9pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#x2022;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-size:9pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;">The definition of operating cash flow includes cash outflow consumed by vehicle leasing.&nbsp;&nbsp;In order to show our cash flow from operations before leasing activities, proceeds from collateralized lease borrowing need to be added back.&nbsp;&nbsp;When that is done, our operating cash flow was $605 million in Q4.&nbsp;&nbsp;Additional $149 million of net funding was received in Q4 through our vehicle lease warehouse line and tax equity fund to help our cash flows.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.33%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;font-size:9pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:9pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#x2022;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-size:9pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;">Capital expenditures reached $787 million in Q4.  The majority was attributable to Model 3 and Gigafactory 1 production capacity increases.  We are continuing to proactively manage capex spending.&nbsp;&nbsp;Additionally, some capex payments for Model 3 have been deferred to Q1.&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:9pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><br /></p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="text-align:justify;margin-bottom:6pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:9pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU4"></a><font style="text-decoration:underline;">OUTLOOK </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;color:#000000;font-size:9pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">2018 will be a <font style="color:#000000;">transformative </font>year for Tesla, with a high level of operational scaling.&nbsp;&nbsp;As we ramp production of both Model 3 and our energy products while keeping tight control of operating expenses, our quarterly operating income should turn sustainably positive at some point in 2018. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;color:#000000;font-size:9pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">We expect Model S and Model X deliveries to be approximately 100,000 in total, constrained by the supply of cells with the old 18650 form factor.&nbsp;&nbsp;As our sales network continues to expand to new markets in 2018, we believe orders should continue to grow.&nbsp;&nbsp;With demand outpacing production, we plan to optimize the options mix in order to maximize gross margin.&nbsp;&nbsp;As stated above, we continue to target a weekly Model 3 production rate of 2,500 by the end of Q1 and 5,000 by the end of Q2.&nbsp;&nbsp;Also, we are focused on achieving our target of 25% gross margin for Model 3 after our production stabilizes at 5,000 cars per week.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;color:#000000;font-size:9pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">We expect energy storage products to experience significant growth, with our aim to at least triple our sales this year.&nbsp;&nbsp;We expect energy generation and storage gross margin to improve significantly in 2018 as we enter the year with a backlog of higher-margin commercial solar projects and a more profitable energy storage business due to manufacturing efficiencies from scaling.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;color:#000000;font-size:9pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Service and Other gross margin should improve in each subsequent quarter in 2018.&nbsp;&nbsp;This will be achieved mainly through improved service productivity via Mobile Service and better remote diagnostics for Model 3.&nbsp;&nbsp;Diagnostics architecture has been substantially redesigned for Model 3 in order to reduce physical service visits by more than 50%.&nbsp;&nbsp;Additionally, Superchargers will start generating revenue in 2018 with pay per use charging primarily by Model 3 customers.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;color:#000000;font-size:9pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Capital expenditures in 2018 are projected to be slightly more than 2017.&nbsp;&nbsp;The majority of the spending will be to support increases in production capacity at Gigafactory 1 and Fremont, and for building stores, service centers, and Superchargers. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;color:#000000;font-size:9pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">This year, we are starting a new chapter of our journey.&nbsp;&nbsp;Hundreds of thousands of people will switch to our EVs and many others will turn their houses into near self-sufficient energy generators.  This is the year when we believe we can achieve true cost parity - producing a premium EV like the Model 3 will be no more expensive than producing an ICE vehicle, something that many believe is not yet possible.&nbsp;&nbsp;We&#8217;ll continue to work as hard as we can to bring sustainable energy generation, storage and consumption into the mainstream. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:9pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="text-decoration:underline;"><br /></font></p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="text-align:justify;margin-bottom:6pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:9pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU5"></a><font style="text-decoration:underline;">WEBCAST INFORMATION </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;color:#000000;font-size:9pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Tesla will provide a live webcast of its fourth quarter and full year 2017 financial results conference call beginning at 2:30 p.m. PT on February 7, 2018, at ir.tesla.com. This webcast will also be available for replay for approximately one year thereafter. </p>
<p style="text-align:justify;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;;font-size:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;;font-size:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;margin-bottom:6pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:9pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="text-decoration:underline;">NON-GAAP FINANCIAL INFORMATION </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;color:#000000;font-size:9pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Consolidated financial information has been presented in accordance with GAAP as well as on a non-GAAP basis to supplement our consolidated financial results. Our non-GAAP financial measures include non-GAAP gross margin, non-GAAP net income (loss) attributable to common stockholders, non-GAAP net income (loss) attributable to common stockholders on a per share basis, and operating cash flows plus change in collateralized lease borrowing. Management believes that it is useful to supplement its GAAP financial statements with this non-GAAP information because management uses such information internally for its operating, budgeting and financial planning purposes. These non-GAAP financial measures also facilitate management&#8217;s internal comparisons to Tesla&#8217;s historical performance as well as comparisons to the operating results of other companies. Management also believes that presentation of the non-GAAP financial measures provides useful information to our investors regarding our financial condition and results of operations because it allows investors greater transparency to the information used by Tesla management in its financial and operational decision-making so that investors can see through the eyes of Tesla management regarding important financial metrics that Tesla management uses to run the business as well as allows investors to better understand Tesla&#8217;s performance. Non-GAAP information is not prepared under a comprehensive set of accounting rules and therefore, should only be read in conjunction with financial information reported under U.S. GAAP when understanding Tesla&#8217;s operating performance. A reconciliation between GAAP and non-GAAP financial information is provided below. </p>
<p style="text-align:justify;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;;font-size:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;;font-size:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;margin-bottom:6pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:9pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="text-decoration:underline;">FORWARD-LOOKING STATEMENTS </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;color:#000000;font-size:9pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Certain statements in this shareholder letter, including statements in the &#8220;Outlook&#8221; section; statements relating to the progress Tesla is making with respect to product and software development, such as Model 3, Solar Roof and Autopilot; statements regarding growth in the number of Tesla store, service center, delivery hub, Supercharger and destination charger locations and in other service and repair capabilities; statements relating to the production, production rate and delivery timing of products such as Model&#160;3, energy storage and Solar Roof; statements regarding growth of our energy generation and storage business and means to achieve such growth; growth in demand and orders for Tesla products and the catalysts for that growth; the ability to achieve product demand, volume, production, delivery, inventory, deployment, revenue, cash generation, cash flow, leasing, gross margin, spending, capital expenditure and profitability targets; productivity improvements and capacity expansion plans, such as for Gigafactory&#160;1; and statements regarding Gigafactory&#160;1 and Gigafactory 2 timing, plans and output expectations, including those related to battery and photovoltaic cell and other production, are &#8220;forward-looking statements&#8221; that are subject to risks and uncertainties. These forward-looking statements are based on management&#8217;s current expectations, and as a result of certain risks and uncertainties, actual results may differ materially from those projected. The following important factors, without limitation, could cause actual results to differ materially from those in the forward-looking statements: the risk of delays in the manufacture, production, delivery and/or completion of our vehicles and energy products, particularly Model 3; the ability to design and achieve and grow simultaneous and separate market acceptance of Model S, Model X and their variants, as well as new vehicle models, specifically Model 3; the ability of suppliers to meet quality and part delivery expectations at increasing volumes, especially with respect to Model 3 parts; any failures by Tesla products to perform as expected or if product recalls occur; Tesla&#8217;s ability to continue to reduce or control manufacturing and other costs; consumers&#8217; willingness to adopt electric vehicles; competition in the automotive and energy product markets generally and the alternative fuel vehicle market and the premium sedan, premium SUV and small to medium-sized sedan markets in particular; Tesla&#8217;s ability to establish, maintain and strengthen the Tesla brand; Tesla&#8217;s ability to manage future growth effectively as we rapidly grow, especially internationally; the unavailability, reduction or elimination of government and economic incentives for electric vehicles and energy products; Tesla&#8217;s ability to establish, maintain and strengthen its relationships with strategic partners such as Panasonic; potential difficulties in finalizing, performing and realizing potential benefits under definitive agreements for Gigafactory&#160;1 and Gigafactory 2, maintaining Gigafactory&#160;1 and Gigafactory 2 implementation schedules, output and cost estimates; Tesla&#8217;s ability to execute on its strategy for new store, delivery hub, service center, Supercharger and other locations and capabilities; and adverse foreign exchange movements. More information on potential factors that could affect our financial results is included from time to time in our Securities and Exchange Commission filings and reports, including the risks identified under the section captioned &#8220;Risk Factors&#8221; in our quarterly report on Form 10-Q filed with the SEC on November&#160;3, 2017. Tesla disclaims any obligation to update information contained in these forward-looking statements whether as a result of new information, future events, or otherwise.</p>

<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;color:#000000;font-size:9pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(2) As of December 31, 2017, our common stock price exceeded the conversion threshold price of our convertible senior notes due in</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;color:#000000;font-size:9pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;2018 (2018 Notes) issued in May 2013; therefore, the 2018 Notes were convertible at the holder&#8217;s option. As such, the carrying</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;color:#000000;font-size:9pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;value of the 2018 Notes was classified as a current liability and the difference between the principal amount and the carrying value</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;color:#000000;font-size:9pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;of the 2018 Notes was reflected as convertible debt in mezzanine equity, on our condensed consolidated balance sheet as of</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;color:#000000;font-size:9pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;December 31, 2017.</p></td>

<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;color:#000000;font-size:9pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&nbsp;</p></td>
